Hi,not sure if this manage to response back to the thread. That problem occurs when the Jpeg starting pixel breaks.....like the starting bits is missing. That occurs for me when I transferred images from a system to another via USB. You have to check if the base64 is still 100% intact, the image will view ok, but you will see the base64 is different. If the image is correct then it will train correctly.

body:
Hi,not sure if this manage to response back to the thread. That problem
occurs when the Jpeg starting pixel breaks.....like the starting bits is
missing. That occurs for me when I transferred images from a system to
another via USB. You have to check if the base64 is still 100% intact, the
image will view ok, but you will see the base64 is different. If the image
is correct then it will train correctly.
